# About Me

## ENG

### who i am

I'm an electronics technician graduated in 2019 at the Federal Institute of Santa Catarina (IFSC) (put link), who now strives to get an undergraduate degree in Electronical Engineering at the Federal University of Santa Catarina (UFSC) (put link). Currently, I live in Florianópolis, Brazil, where, in addition to studying engineering, I study programming on my own. When I'm not designing new circuits, studying or coding, I like to play some basketball or soccer, to read and to sing -- sometimes mixing things up too...

### what i do

As an electronic technician, I integrate digital and analog circuits choosing the best components depending on the situation I'm handling. My arsenal includes the general applications IC's, operational amplifiers, regulators and so on. I can also manage programming microcontrollers with the C language, making them communicate with other devices. For the past 4 years, I've been studying, working and researching electronics. Among that time I've also developed the ability to design printed circuit boards with softwares such as Altium, Proteus and KiCAD.

Most recently, I've been studying Web Development. My stack includes Node.js, Vue.js, HTML5, CSS3, Bootstrap and also some relational and non-relational databases, such as PostgresSQL and MongoDB. Please be free to check me out on GitHub (put link)!

